cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with extreme multi-label text classification, which is a problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a deep learning model, which makes it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of attention mechanisms and probabilistic label trees also suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
